# age recipients file — one public recipient per line.
#
# Real file must live OUTSIDE the repo at:
#   /root/.keys/age-recipients.txt      (public, used by backup script)
#   /root/.keys/age-identity.txt        (PRIVATE, used by restore script)
#
# Never commit the real files. This .example is only a format reference.
#
# Generate a key pair with:
#   age-keygen -o /root/.keys/age-identity.txt
# The public recipient is the line in that file starting with "# public key:".
# Copy the recipient (the line WITHOUT the comment prefix) into the
# recipients file:
#
# age1qyqszqgpqyqszqgpqyqszqgpqyqszqgpqyqszqgpqyqszqgpqyqszqexample
#
# You can add multiple recipients (one per line) if multiple humans need
# to be able to decrypt.
